Name: Solo Todt - 290k firemaking, 15k con, 10k woodcutting xp/hr
Description: Doing solo wintertodt is the best points per hour, which can be useful for those either seeking more loot or construction xp from wintertodt. The videos do a good job at explaining the method. For more details, refer to https://pastebin.com/vbvf2RXU.

Name: World 9 Wintertodt - 330k firemaking, 4.4k construction, 20k woodcutting xp/hr

Videos.Title: Celastrus barking to start cutting earlier example
Fletching a log while lighting brazier

Description: After killing the wintertodt, use your house pool and then do a bank skill between rounds. Any skill where you can drop / use the output e.g. crafting glass / wines / log firemaking are best because you can do it while running to and while inside the wintertodt area. You can fletch a log while lighting the braziers, and walk out of the way when you see heavy snowfall above the brazier.

Name: World-hop Wintertodt (380k+ xp/h at level 99)
Description: Use alts to scout a half-finished Wintertodt world. Fletch the bruma roots to get 500 points as quickly as possible. Use all tricks in Method #2 to maximize efficiency. This method can reach up to 400k firemaking xp/h, but the long-term rate is closer to 370k-380k.
